Build ID: 4.4.0.3
Steps To Reproduce: 1.Import the attached log file in LA-RCP 2.Create a highlighter as follow: Attribute Operator Value Message Text = *SNMP* 3.Show highlighted events only Note that the bottom event is not highlighted.
More information:
Created attachment 86566 patch for the head stream

Hi Alex,
Eric found this problem and opened a high severity defect in AC. So we'd like to see this problem get fixed by the end of this week. But the fix needs to be checked into TPTP cvs. Could you please review the patch and add it in the 4.4.0.3 patch for us?
Thanks
================================================================= This error occurs when highlighted events are in different pages.
When a user selects "Show highlighted events only", a property changed event is fired. In LogLabelProvider, the property change listener used to call "updateHiglighRecordInPage()" to get the highlighted events in the current visible page, and then call viewer.refresh to rebuild and redraw the page. When highlighted events are in different pages, events from pages other than the visible page will not get highlighted in "updateHiglighRecordInPage ()".
Fixed this in the listener by calling viewer.refresh before "updateHiglighRecordInPage()", which will make sure the current page gets updated with all filtered in events, so that "updateHiglighRecordInPage ()" will get events that need to be displayed in the current page.
This fix will not cause performance hit. Because what happens when a user selects a filter is the same, ie viewer.refresh will be executed first, "updateHiglighRecordInPage()" and then viewer.refresh again.
The patch is for plugin "org.eclipse.tptp.platform.log.views". =================================================================
